        <article class="recipe-box">
          <h3>1) Greek Yogurt Berry Bowl</h3>
          <p><strong>Why it works:</strong> Cool, creamy, fast, and packed with protein.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>1 cup plain Greek yogurt</li>
            <li>1/2 cup fresh berries</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon chia seeds</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon chopped walnuts</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon honey, optional</li>
          </ul>
          <ol>
            <li>Spoon the yogurt into a bowl.</li>
            <li>Top with berries, chia seeds, and walnuts.</li>
            <li>Finish with a light drizzle of honey if desired.</li>
          </ol>
          <div class="highlight">
            Chef note: For a prettier presentation, layer the berries and nuts in sections instead of mixing everything together.
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="recipe-box">
          <h3>2) Cozy Oatmeal with Fruit</h3>
          <p><strong>Why it works:</strong> Warm, gentle, and easy on the stomach.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>1/2 cup rolled oats</li>
            <li>1 cup milk of choice</li>
            <li>1/2 banana, sliced</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon almond butter</li>
            <li>Pinch of cinnamon</li>
          </ul>
          <ol>
            <li>Simmer oats with milk until soft and creamy.</li>
            <li>Pour into a bowl and top with banana slices.</li>
            <li>Add almond butter and a small pinch of cinnamon.</li>
          </ol>
          <div class="highlight">
            Chef note: Stir in the almond butter while the oats are still warm so it melts into the bowl and adds richness.
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="recipe-box">
          <h3>3) Avocado Toast with Egg</h3>
          <p><strong>Why it works:</strong> Balanced, savory, and satisfying.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>1 slice whole grain toast</li>
            <li>1/2 ripe avocado</li>
            <li>1 cooked egg</li>
            <li>Pinch of salt and black pepper</li>
            <li>Optional: squeeze of lemon</li>
          </ul>
          <ol>
            <li>Toast the bread until golden.</li>
            <li>Mash avocado with a pinch of salt and lemon.</li>
            <li>Spread on toast and top with the cooked egg.</li>
            <li>Season lightly and serve right away.</li>
          </ol>
          <div class="highlight">
            Chef note: A soft scrambled or fully cooked fried egg gives this breakfast a comforting café feel.
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="recipe-box">
